 *1275924293* I made a PONG-like game on my iPad that can be controlled by figures.
 I tried to give a practical demonstration of how <a href="http://www.nishiohirokazu.org/muroto/">Muroto</a> can be used to make a game that uses a figure as a controller. Why are the operations in the latter part of the demo on an iPhone so slow? One reason is that I was holding my iPhone 3GS with one hand while demonstrating with an iPhone 3G with the other hand, so I couldn't move it too fast. As you can see in the first half of the demo, the real-time game on the iPad seems to be able to run at about 30 FPS even if you move the game around.
 
 [http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sPdrRpTsepk:movie]
 
