 >>
 If socialism is defined as the ownership of the means of production by workers, then the United States is the first true socialist nation in history. (omission) Only the U.S. has realized true socialism in the sense that the workers, the source of value in Marxian economics, own the fruits of their productive activities. The U.S. realized the socialization of its economy unintentionally and without nationalization.
 
 In less than a year, four times as many pension funds had been created in the U.S. as had been established in the previous 100 years. In less than a year, four times as many pension funds had been created in the United States in the previous 100 years, and all of them employed the most radical innovations of all GM's pension funds. <b>GM's pension funds were a kind of mutual fund. </b>
